article.description: — Darius Gakwasi scored 18 points as Princeton beat Delaware Valley 84-53 on Friday.
article.headline: Gakwasi puts up 18, Princeton downs Delaware Valley 84-53
article.linkText: Gakwasi puts up 18, Princeton downs Delaware Valley 84-53
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- — Darius Gakwasi scored 18 points as Princeton beat Delaware Valley 84-53 on Friday. Gakwasi shot 7 for 12, including 4 for 7 from beyond the arc for the Tigers (11-1). Vernon Collins scored 11 points while going 3 of 6 and 5 of 5 from the free throw line, and added eight rebounds. Jacob Huggins finished 4 of 6 from the floor to finish with 10 points. Antonio Redding finished with seven points for the Aggies. Delaware Valley also got seven points from Rasheem Dearry. Tyriq Toney-Bailey also had six points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
